<li> Gym Beginner Guide (Brief) </li>

<ol> <li>Frequency</li> 

* Train 2–3 days per week.
* Rest at least one day between sessions.

 <li> Workout Focus </li>
* Prioritize compound exercises: squat, deadlift, bench press, overhead press, rows, lat pulldown.
* Full-body workouts are best at the start.

<li> Example Routine </li>

* Squat: 3×5
* Bench press or push-ups: 3×5–8
* Lat pulldown or row: 3×8
* Deadlift: 1×5
* Plank: 2×30–60s

<li> Weights </li>

* Start light.
* Increase weight slowly when all reps feel controlled.

<li> Form & Safety </li>

* Warm up 5–10 minutes.
* Learn proper form before adding weight.
* Stop if something causes pain (not normal muscle fatigue).

<li> Recovery & Nutrition </li>

* Sleep 7–9 hours.
* Eat balanced meals with enough protein.
* Stay hydrated.

Consistency matters more than intensity at the beginning."

